PART: Categories
NAME: Categories
STATUS: draft

TYPE: Budget Category
MARKER: budget_category
INTENT: define spending categories
---
Each category has a name like "Food" or "Entertainment" and a monthly budget limit amount. Categories help organize expenses and set spending boundaries for different areas of life. ---

STATE: Category Collection
MARKER: category_collection
INTENT: store all budget categories
---
The app maintains a list of all budget categories the user has created. Each category includes its name, monthly limit, and current spending total for easy comparison. ---

STRUCTURE: Category List View
MARKER: category_list_view
INTENT: display categories and limits
---
The main view shows each category as a card with its name, monthly budget limit, current spending, and remaining amount. A progress bar visualizes how much of the budget has been used. ---

WHEN: Add New Category
MARKER: add_new_category
INTENT: create spending category
---
User clicks the add button and enters a category name and monthly budget limit. The new category appears in the list with zero current spending and the full budget amount remaining. ---
---PART---

PART: Expenses
NAME: Expenses
STATUS: draft

TYPE: Expense Entry
MARKER: expense_entry
INTENT: record individual purchases
---
Each expense has an amount, description, date, and assigned category. The description helps remember what was purchased while the category links it to the appropriate budget limit. ---

STATE: Expense History
MARKER: expense_history
INTENT: track all spending records
---
The app stores every expense entry with its details and automatically calculates totals by category and date ranges. This running history enables budget tracking and spending analysis. ---

STRUCTURE: Expense Input Form
MARKER: expense_input_form
INTENT: capture new expenses quickly
---
A simple form appears with fields for amount, description, category dropdown, and date picker. The interface prioritizes speed since users often log expenses on the go. ---

WHEN: Record New Expense
MARKER: record_new_expense
INTENT: log recent purchase
---
User enters the expense amount, adds a description, selects a category, and confirms the date. The expense saves immediately and updates the category's current spending total and remaining budget. ---
---PART---

PART: Overview
NAME: Overview
STATUS: draft

STRUCTURE: Budget Dashboard
MARKER: budget_dashboard
INTENT: show overall financial status
---
The dashboard displays total monthly budget, total spent, and remaining amount across all categories. Visual indicators highlight categories that are over budget or approaching their limits. ---

WHEN: View Monthly Summary
MARKER: view_monthly_summary
INTENT: check budget performance
---
User navigates to the overview screen to see spending patterns and budget adherence. The dashboard automatically calculates totals and shows which categories need attention for the current month. ---